The measurement has become a potent expression of social distancing.
Social distancing signs at a park in London.
Around the world, people have devised various ways to denote the prescribed social distancing protocol using chalk marks, tape, floor stickers, signs, furniture and other crafty means.
“Someone walking their dog will give you a 20-foot berth.”Reuters/P Ravikumar Social distancing chalk graffiti at a vegetable market in Chennai, India.
As one example from Thailand shows, it’s virtually impossible to observe social distancing in such tight spaces.